4 Hacking
*********

The print buffer, invoked from 'Control+p', will offer you to eval
things or make (compile).  The insert prompt, invoked from 'Alt+v', will
allow you to insert a file, or the result of an async shell command into
a new buffer.  The save buffer, from 'Alt+s', offers to use git power to
save cats or so.

   'Control+p' also offers to grep, find-grep or ediff.

   As seen above, 'Alt+b' will run an emphasis-prompt, which allows to
comment.  Onto c-mode or various lisp-mode, 'Control+b' will toggle
comments.


